<h3>
    <strong>1. North Santiam River (Below Big Cliff Dam to Stayton)</strong>
</h3>
<ul>
    <li>
        <strong>Species</strong>: Spring Chinook, Coho, and both summer and winter steelhead 
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Peak Season</strong>: Spring Chinook (May–June), Coho (Sept–Oct), Summer Steelhead (June–July) .
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Access</strong>: River parks and boat launches near Mehama, Stayton–Scio Bridge, Mill City, and below Big Cliff 
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Tactics</strong>: Trolling plugs, drift spinners, float rigs with roe; fly anglers can find native trout too&nbsp;
    </li>
</ul>
<h3>
    <strong>2. South Santiam River (Below Foster Dam to Waterloo Bridge)</strong>
</h3>
<ul>
    <li>
        <strong>Species</strong>: Spring Chinook, natural and hatchery Coho, and steelhead 
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Season</strong>: Chinook peak in May–July; Coho and winter steelhead run from mid-fall through spring 
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Access</strong>: Bank fishing at Foster Dam, Pleasant Valley Bridge, Waterloo Park, and near Sweet Home
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Tips</strong>: Bait rigs, spinners, and plugs work well; bait permitted Apr–Oct&nbsp;
    </li>
</ul>
<h3>
    <strong>3. Mainstem Santiam River (Below Forks to Confluence with Willamette)</strong>
</h3>
<ul>
    <li>
        <strong>Species</strong>: Spring Chinook, Coho, Steelhead 
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Season</strong>: Chinook (May–July), Coho (Sept–Oct), Steelhead (Summer &amp; Winter) .
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Access</strong>: Pullouts and boat ramps near Stayton, Jefferson, and downstream approaching the Willamette
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Tactics</strong>: Drifting plugs or roe rigs near confluences and holding holes .
    </li>
</ul>
<h3>
    <strong>4. Willamette River (Near Salem)</strong>
</h3>
<ul>
    <li>
        <strong>Species</strong>: Spring Chinook, Coho, Steelhead 
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Season</strong>: Chinook (April–May), Coho (Sept–Nov), Steelhead (summer/winter runs) 
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Access</strong>: Parks and ramps along the Willamette near Salem, including river landings downstream of the Santiam confluence 
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Approach</strong>: Float rigs, plugs, and trolling are effective near the river junction.
    </li>
</ul>
<h3>
    <strong>5. Siuslaw River (Day Trip Option)</strong>
</h3>
<ul>
    <li>
        <strong>Species</strong>: Fall Chinook and winter steelhead 
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Season</strong>: Chinook run strong from September to October; winter steelhead January–March .
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Access</strong>: Estuary and upstream at Cushman/Mapleton; drift boats launchable at Whittaker Creek 
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Tactics</strong>: Back-trolling Hot-Shots, spinners, and roe rigs in both estuary and upriver spaces.
    </li>
</ul>
